Cleaning the Data

In [116]:
# merging different DFs caused column names to be included in the rows
# Convert everything in order id to numeric and whatever is non-numeric, coerce
# them to be considered as NaN and just extract the values which are non-NAN

numeric_order_ids = pd.to_numeric(merged_df['Order ID'], errors = 'coerce')
cleaned_merged_data = merged_df[numeric_order_ids.notna()]
cleaned_merged_data.to_csv("Cleaned_Merged_Sales_Data.csv", index = False)

# count of pair of items ordered together
from itertools import combinations
from collections import Counter

count = Counter()

for row in duplicate_df['Grouped']:
  row_list = row.split(',')
  count.update(Counter(combinations(row_list, 2)))
